history.text: Hi there, I would like to talk to you about the movie Inception, do you like sci-fi at all?
Sometimes
Depending on the subject metter
matter
What is the movie about?
This is a Leonardo DiCaprio film where he attempts to steal information from individual's subconscious via dreams.
Is it violent>

There are violent scenes but I would say not as much compared to other movies. H
e meets his match when he attempts this with a Japanese businessman.
Is there a mystery in the story, or is it pretty straight forward?
The concept and story is actually very detailed as they enlist the help of a traditional architect graduate to help construct the various dreamscapes they use in their missions.
There is a mixture of different metaphors built in to the movie which some believe relate to the power of delusion.
So it's like a psychological kind of movie? I'm assuming
Does it mess with what is real and what is dreamed up?

Exactly that, a major part of the movie involves a dying business man and a son who is to inherit his fortune.  They take an opportunity during a flight to enter a dream phase to steel information and influence the target.
There are many levels that go deeper within the dream, dreamscapes withing dreamscapes to the point the individual cannot tell what is real.
That sounds like an interesting movie
A member of the team must stay behind to set up a "kick" which they use to pull people out of the dreamscapes.
Are there any other big name actors, or just Di caprio?
Sounds intense!
The movie itself is directed by Christopher Nolan and there are other famous actors within the movie; Joseph Gordon-Levitt as an example.
How long is the movie?
I would really recommend the movie, I don't want to give too much away of the plot as you will enjoy every minute.
It does sound interesting!
It's an average length of approximately 90 minutes but will have you thinking continually throughout
So it's a brain bender? :D

100%, their goal during the flight is to plan a 'seed' in the mind of the son to inherit his dead father's fortune.  Leonardo accepts the mission as it is the only way he can see his children again, who were left in care following his framed murder charge.
Is it an older move? When did it come out?
Is is a 2009 movie and had average review rating of 8.1 out of 10 on Rotten Tomatoes and 8.8 out of 10 on IMDB!
So it's a popular one

Tom Hardy plays Leonardo's counter part through the whole mission and excellent in the role.  Reviews at the time felt that the movie would draw people in to it's love story regarding Leonardo's wife in the movie and that it would appeal to non-sci-fi fans also.
Really, you should take the opportunity to watch it, you won't be disappointed!
Sounds fascinating

uid2response.feedback: I already watched the movie when it first came out. The person I was speaking with was very lively, and sold the movie well.
